                                                            ASSIGNMENT 2

1. Created a form having fields - first name, last name, gender(radio button), Date of Birth(datepicker), select role(dropdown - developer, tester, manager, team leader), skills(checkboxes - Java, NodeJs, React, Angular, Android), About employee(Text area max 300 characters)															
2. Appllied proper validations and shown error message															
3. Added loader after submitting form															
4. Shown added record in table and success/error message to end user															
5. Shown delete and update actions in Actions column															
6. Updated record should display in table															
7. In backend employeeId should get generate automatically and use this for update and delete record


Used Json-server for backend 


To Run a Project follow below steps
Start two powershell
In first run project localhost:4200/  http://localhost:4200/

In second powershell start json server
command : json-server --watch db.json 
Resources
  http://localhost:3000/registerEmployee

Home
  http://localhost:3000



Used Angular Material for making form and Table
Command : ng add @angular/material

Used bootstrap Framework
Command : npm install --save bootstrap  
Updated in angular.json